ses who are primarily offense. Verant must keep this in mind when deciding how many seconds should pass till the next increment in attack speed. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I think it's a creative suggestion, but I also think it really cripples groups that are already less-than-optimal.  Consider this extremely common scenario: it's an off night in your guild, and there are 2 druids, 1 mage, a paladin, and a bard LFG.  Well, you have healers and a tank, bard slow/CC, and some dps, but this group will have a very obvious disadvantage against mobs that become gradually hasted over time (or un-slowed over time).  They don't have the dps to kill faster, and while they may have the healing to cover the increase in damage, their downtime will be much greater due to the druid's lesser heals.  Currently, at least with the bard's marginal slow and the druid's marginal CH, they can still manage to keep up a fair pace.  Not optimal, but fair.<br>
<br>
It also does very little or nothing to eliminate the cleric dependency.  If the mob's damage increases exponentially, so does the healing power required.  Slowers actually help mutt groups by knocking out at least one of the &quot;trinity&quot; (cleric), often times two (cleric &amp; warrior) because it makes it easier for lesser tank classes to handle the job.  You say you want the trinity to die, but by gradually hasting mobs or having slow wear off, what you're doing is locking down yet another slot or two for a nuker/dps class.  That's great if you're a nuker like we are, but it sucks to be the bards, paladins, and other lower-dps classes of the world, whose potential to get in a group just dropped to 2/6ths instead of one half.<br>
<br>
Like I said, it's creative, but I think you're overlooking some pretty major drawbacks (or, inconveniences).  I think you've also forgotten the natural tendancy for EQ players to seek out the most optimal group configuration for the situation.  If mob dps starts to increase exponentially over the duration of a fight, it will lead even more groups to <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>require</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> the right tools to handle the new challenge, which is still the &quot;holy trinity.&quot;  And those people who are LFG on experience night are still left LFG. <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.dark-bane.com/mageloframes/sambusframe.htm">Sambus Veneficus</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Arch Mage of Ak'anon, 63<br>
Member, <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.dark-bane.com">Dark Bane</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
Mithaniel Marr Server<br>
